---
title: Hoisin Stir-Fry with Brown Rice, Sugar Snap Peas, and Ginger
description: We get this stir-fry off to a flavorful start with the aromatic trifecta of ginger, onion, and garlic. And although it’s got all the traditional veggies you’d expect to find, there’s also some eggplant tossed in there for added bulk and nutrition.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/uk-body-boosting-hoisin-stir-fry-91f740a2.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/uk-body-boosting-hoisin-stir-fry-610c84db.pdf
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Asian
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 647 kcal
  fat: 18 g
  saturated fat: 2 g
  carbohydrates: 112 g
  sugar: 27 g
  protein: 18 g
  fiber: 17 g
  sodium: 339 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hoisin-stir-fry-57e2c282383a7f6eb96b7533
course: main course
---

Place @Brown Rice{3/4%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} in a medium #pot{} with enough water to cover it by 3 inches. Bring to a boil. Cook until tender, about ~{25%minutes}, then drain (just like pasta).

Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and thinly slice @Yellow Bell Pepper{1%unit} into thin slices. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1%unit}. Thinly slice @Scallions{2%unit}. Peel and mince @Ginger{1%thumb}. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Trim @Sugar Snap Peas{6%ounce}. Cut @Lime{1%unit} into wedges. Mince @Chili Pepper{1%unit}. TIP: Remove seeds if you prefer less heat.

Prep the eggplant: Cut @Eggplant{1%unit} into 1-inch cubes, and toss in #medium bowl{} with @Cornstarch{1%tablespoon} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @Pepper{}.

Cook the eggplant: Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Work in batches to cook eggplant cubes until softened and browned on all sides, ~{5-7%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat another large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add onions, garlic, scallions, ginger, and chili pepper (to taste). Toss until just barely softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add bell peppers. Cook until softened, another ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

Add sugar snap peas. Cook until crisp-tender, another ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in eggplant, cilantro, 3 Tablespoons @Hoisin Sauce Jar{2%jar}, and a squeeze of lime. Toss until thoroughly heated through, about ~{1%minute}. Serve the hoisin stir-fry on a bed of brown rice. Sprinkle with @Peanuts{1%ounce}, serve with lime wedges, and enjoy!